title: California Housing Data
description: In this project, I'm focused on a revised version of the California Housing Data originally explored in Pace and Barry's paper on Sparse Spatial Autoregressions (Statistics & Probability Letters, 1997). Derived from the 1990 California census

title: World Happiness Data
description: The dataset ranks 157 countries by happiness score, considering factors like GDP, family, life expectancy, freedom, government corruption, generosity, and dystopia residual.

title: National Flood Insurance Program
description: The National Flood Insurance Program (NFIP) is the main provider of flood insurance in the United States, partnering with private insurers to offer coverage within participating communities. Analysis of flooding, particularly during the 2016 to 2019 hurricane seasons, underscores its significant economic impact
